	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-06T07:39:02">Andes Energia plc (Andes) is a United Kingdom-based oil and gas company focused on onshore blocks in South America. The Company has interests in Argentina, Colombia, Brazil and Paraguay. Andes holds interests in exploration, development and producing assets. The Company has around 20 million barrels (bbls) of conventional 2P reserves in Argentina and certified resources of 640 million barrel of oil equivalent (boe). The Company's licenses cover around 7.5 million acres across South America with two million net acres in unconventional plays, including 250,000 net acres in the Vaca Muerta formation, a shale oil deposit. The Company produces around 1,952 barrels per day (bpd) in Argentina from six conventional fields.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-01T08:30:49">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Andes Energia PLC revenues increased 60% to $32.5M. Net loss increased 19% to $3.2M. Revenues reflect an increase in demand for the Company's products and services due to favorable market conditions. Higher net loss reflects Administrativeexpenses increase from $2.9M to $9.2M (expense), Financecosts increase from $3.6M to $7.8M (expense), Distributioncosts increase of 28% to $2.2M (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
